OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1778351318
OL,3,CMore than 200,000 migrants have
OL,4,Ccrossed the Channel in small boats
OL,5,Csince 2018
OL,7,FAt least 17 people died while
OL,8,Fattempting the journey in 2025,
OL,9,Faccording to reports by French and UK
OL,10,Fauthorities.
OL,12,FThe International Organisation for
OL,13,FMigration (IOM) has also reported more
OL,14,Fmigrant deaths believed to be linked
OL,15,Fto crossing attempts.
OL,17,FThe first migrant known to have
OL,18,Fdrowned while attempting the crossing
OL,19,Fwas a 31-year-old Iranian woman, Mitra
OL,20,FMehrad, in August 2019.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/12
